<TITLE> BAF's 'Fire Power 2008' captivates crowd </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh Air Force's annual firing exercise 'Fire Power-2008' rounded off on Tuesday with a "spectacular show that kept guests spell-bound" at the Firing Range in Tangail. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed, attending the exercise as chief guest, was cordially received by chief of air staff air marshal SM Ziaur Rahman, who presented a BAF crest to the CA on the occasion, said an ISPR press release. "Different types of fighter aircrafts, transport aircrafts and helicopters took part in the exercise. Following various modern tactics of air warfare those aircraft carried out air to ground live firing with bullets, rockets and bombs on various targets" said the statement. "Air Power is an indispensable part of moder warfare ... In today's demonstration, BAF also pilots displayed a partial fire power of BAF, which is essential in safeguarding the sovereignty of the country," it added. Advisers, diplomats, chiefs of three armed forces and top civil and military officials were among those present on the occasion. bd
